Finance Minister Nirmala Sitharaman presented her 8th Union Budget to the Parliament on 1st February 2025. The Budget covered different proposals for the Indian Economy.
In this video, Abhi and Niyu have covered important points from the Budget proposals, explained how the new tax slabs and rebate works, and explain how the Union Budget works. 

Here are some of the important proposals mentioned in the Budget:
* Nuclear Energy Mission
* Support to Footwear Industry (both leather and non leather)
* Makhana Board for Bihar
* Support to Make in India Toys
* Shipbuilding Financial Assistance Policy
* Policy to procure pulses directly from farmers on contract farming basis
* Modified UDAN scheme
* National Repository of Indian Knowledge books
* Bharat TRADENET
* High Level Committee for non financial sector regulatory reforms

Finance Minister Nirmala Sitharaman presented her 8th Union Budget to the Parliament on 1st February 2025. The Budget covered different proposals for the Indian Economy.
In this video, Abhi and Niyu have covered important points from the Budget proposals, explained how the new tax slabs and rebate works, and explain how the Union Budget works. 

Here are some of the important proposals mentioned in the Budget:
* Nuclear Energy Mission
* Support to Footwear Industry (both leather and non leather)
* Makhana Board for Bihar
* Support to Make in India Toys
* Shipbuilding Financial Assistance Policy
* Policy to procure pulses directly from farmers on contract farming basis
* Modified UDAN scheme
* National Repository of Indian Knowledge books
* Bharat TRADENET
* High Level Committee for non financial sector regulatory reforms

Sources: 
Economic Survey: https://www.indiabudget.gov.in/economicsurvey/
Budget: https://www.indiabudget.gov.in/

snippet.title: Saraswati Vandana | Shreya Ghoshal
snippet.description:
Shreya Ghoshal embarks on a new musical journey with devotion at its heart, beginning with a Saraswati Vandana‚Äîa sacred ode to the goddess of wisdom, music, and the arts. This newly composed hymn beautifully captures the essence of Ma Saraswati‚Äôs grace, symbolising the purity of mind, intellectual and spiritual enlightenment and creativity. Enriched by the ethereal voice of Shreya Ghoshal, whose pristine vocal texture brings unmatched beauty, the melody flows like a sacred offering, uplifting the soul and invoking the goddess‚Äôs blessings. Her vocals seamlessly weave into the poignant notes of Sarod and the lush choral arrangements. This musical offering is an invitation to immerse in the profound peace and inspiration that Ma Saraswati personifies.

(Salutations to Goddess Saraswati)

Om

Ya Kundendu Tusharharadhavala
(She who is as white as the jasmine flower, the moon, and a garland of snow)

Ya Kundendu Tusharaharadhavala
(She who is as white as the jasmine flower, the moon, and a garland of snow)

Ya Shubhra Vastravrita
(She who is adorned with pure white garments)

Ya Veena Varadanda ManditaKara
(She whose hands are adorned with the divine veena)

Ya Shweta Padmasana
(She who is seated on a white lotus throne)

Ya Brahmachyuta Shankara Prabhritibhir Devai Sada Pujita
(She who is always worshiped by Brahma, Vishnu, and Shiva)


Sa Maam Patu Saraswati Bhagavati Nishesh Jaadyapaha
(May that goddess Saraswati, who removes all ignorance, protect me.)

(Salutations and reverence to Goddess Saraswati)

Om

snippet.title: School Ka Sports Day | Take A Break
snippet.description:
Ah, School Ka Sports Day‚Äîthe one day when even the laziest kids suddenly become athletes (at least in spirit)! üòú
In this hilarious sketch, we take you back to those unforgettable moments of school sports day, filled with awkward races, overenthusiastic teachers, biased referees, and parents acting like it‚Äôs the Olympics! üèÖ From kids faking injuries to avoid running, to the epic rivalry in the lemon-and-spoon race, we've captured it all in the most relatable way possible.
Share with your your school buddies and relive the madness together! üéΩü§£

Jaane Tu, Jaanu Main‚Ä¶

For the powerful love behind the powerful warrior, ‚ÄòJaane Tu‚Äô is a romantic ballad for the ages. Combining the three maestros of music ‚Äì A. R. Rahman, Arijit Singh and Irshad Kamil, it features Vicky Kaushal and Rashmika Mandanna in the video.  From the highly anticipated movie ‚ÄòChhaava‚Äô, this is the first song release from the movie.

#JaaneTu #ARRahman #ArijitSingh #IrshadKamil #VickyKaushal #RashmikaMandanna #AkshayeKhanna #Chhaava 

üéµStream Now: https://smi.lnk.to/JaaneTu

Song Credits:
Music composed, produced, and arranged by A.R. Rahman
Vocals - Arijit Singh
Lyrics - Irshad Kamil
Music Supervisor & Editor - Hiral Viradia

Musicians:
Flute - Navin Kumar
Bass - Keith Peters
Sarod - Pratik Shrivastava
Tabla - Sai Shravanam
Additional programming- Parag Chhabra, Japjisingh Valecha, Shubham Bhatt, Sarthak Kalyani
Chorus - Aanandi Joshi, Sumedha Karmahe, Aasa Singh, Sudeep Jaipurwale
Mixed and Mastered by - Nitish R Kumar

Strings recorded by Budapest Scoring Orchestra

Maddock Films presents #Chhaava
Releasing in cinemas on 14th February.

Produced By Dinesh Vijan
Directed By: Laxman Utekar
Co-Producers: Sharada Karki Jalota, Pooja Prem Patheja
Original Songs & Background Score: A R Rahman
Adapted Story, Screenplay By: Laxman Utekar, Rishi Virmani, Kaustubh Savarkar, Unman Bankar, Omkar Mahajan
Lyrics & Additional Dialogue: Irshad Kamil
Dialogue: Rishi Virmani
Director Of Photography: Saurabh Goswami (Isc)

Lyrics:

Jaane tu jaanun main
Meri jaan tu hi Thi tu hi hai
Ye saansein kya saansein
Inka aana jaana yun hi hai
Meri Jaan tu Hai
Tu thi haan tu hai
Jaane tu jaanun main

Tere honthon honthon pe vaade mere
Tere honthon honthon pe baatein meri
Chain jaisa tera khayal
Dheere dheere aaye

Mere honthon honthon pe vaade tere
Mere honthon honthon pe baatein teri
Lafz mere lena sanbhaal
In mein tere saaye

Dekho kya kya bataayein
Baagi hawayein
Dheeme suron mein gaayein... ho

Jaane tu jaanun main
Meri jaan tu hi thi tu hi hai
Ye saansein kya saansein
Inka aana jaana yun hi hai
Meri Jaan tu Hai
Tu thi haan tu hai
Jaane tu jaanun main

Kya dard hai
Kya chot hai
Tere khayal mein hun
Mujhko na hosh hai

Tu saath hai mere
Lahu mein hai khushi
Maine na tootna
Main vaada hun tumhara

snippet.title: Dilli Ki Winters | The Paayal Jain
snippet.description:
Hey Guys , 
Hope you enjoy this winter video . We love you so much .

Click on Link To Buy Himalaya Serum - https://amzn.to/3EaXbc2

This video shows different behaviours of Indians during winters . Dilli Ki Winters is extreme .  This is a very comic and relatable video. When the temperature is falling and the heaters , hot water bags , heating pads , sweaters , sweatshirts , hoodies , coats , jackets , scarfs mufflers , gloves , thermals , socks , monkey caps , boots , comes to beat the cold especially if it's delhi winters . College exams during winters , School Board Exams with hot coffee or tea travelling by metro bikes in thand , shopping from sarojini market for latest winter fashion , planning winter trip to hills with friends to see snow , cause snowfall , bonfire with friends is the best time . indian moms covering kids in multiple layers of warm clothes to avoid cold and flue , Feeding winter green leafy vegetables , hara saag and  enjoying thand me gajar ka halwa , lazy winters in bed watching shows Tv serials anupama or christmas movies with hot chocolate , chai , heater , blanket perfect cosy environment .  Buying school winter uniform for kids , Mothers and their millions of excuses when it comes to exercising or changing life in sardiyan that sardi bht pad rhi he and alot more . All these winter problems that we all indians in winters face .

This video is filled with such memories and situations we all have been in. 
Relish and Relive your Memories.. You will love this .
Do share it with your friends and family  .. Comment down your Fav Part,

snippet.title: Celebrating the Year of the Snake! üêç Clash of Clans New Season
snippet.description:
Legendary snakes of the Clash lands are ushering in an age of celebration! Get in on the Lunar festivities, unleash mystical Snake Heroes, and start training for some ludicrously Lunar challenges and Events ahead! Visit the sky-high home of the ancient elemental snakes with the Year of the Snake Legendary Scenery and transform your Village into a serene sanctuary where the celebrations never end!

Follow us on our Socials!
Twitter ‚ñ∫ https://twitter.com/ClashofClans/
Instagram ‚ñ∫ https://www.instagram.com/clashofclans

From rage-¬≠filled Barbarians with glorious mustaches to pyromaniac wizards, raise your own army and lead your clan to victory! Build your village to fend off raiders, battle against millions of players worldwide, and forge a powerful clan with others to destroy enemy clans.
PLEASE NOTE! Clash of Clans is free to download and play, however some game items can also be purchased for real money 

Also, under our Terms of Service and Privacy Policy, you must be at least 13 years of age to play or download Clash of Clans.
A network connection is also required.

FEATURES
- Build your village into an unbeatable fortress 
- Raise your own army of Barbarians, Archers, Hog Riders, Wizards, Dragons and other mighty fighters
- Battle with players worldwide and take their Trophies
- Join together with other players to form the ultimate Clan
- Fight against rival Clans in epic Clan Wars 
- Build 18 unique units with multiple levels of upgrades
- Discover your favorite attacking army from countless combinations of troops, spells, Heroes and Clan reinforcements 
- Defend your village with a multitude of Cannons, Towers, Mortars, Bombs, Traps and Walls
- Fight against the Goblin King in a campaign through the realm

Chief, are you having problems? Visit https://help.supercellsupport.com/clash-of-clans/en/

snippet.description:

AFSOS (Lyrics)

A 1

Haan 
Teri yaadan yaadan 
Teri yaadan le ke betha 
Kai raatan raatan

Par aaj
Ena raatan picho
Meinu sab sach nazar ae aunda
Kivein akhan akhan?

B 1

Jo guroor si 
Oh fizool si 
Meinu aaj pata laga 
Ki kasoor si 

Mere dil de noor 
Main si mash-hoor 
Tenu karta dur 
Oh, bekasoor!

Kinj gairan nu 
Main apna mann 
Mileya mere apne nu 
Gair ban

Eh taan zaroor 
Dil karta choor
Tera

C 1 

Te haan
Main duniya vekhi 
Tere dil nu vekh na paya 
Main jhalla jhalla 

Karda si
Wadeya nawan di
Gallan gallan

Hun ethe
Marda janda 
Main kalla kalla

A 2

Hun kyun 
Afsos hoya?
Hun ki fayeda?
Milna ni
Je chahaan chahaan

Main hun
Ghadiya de hath te
Kivein modha 
Rukh samay da 
Te rahaan rahaan?

D 

Chand pal do pal 
Teri sunda battan je 

Tere nal hi 
Sab katda rattan je 

Tere hanju dekhda 
Vich barsattan je

Kitte karda teh 
Eh dil di vattan je 

B 2

Kaisi shaam si
Tere naam si 
Jo padheya na main
Ki pegham si?

Main hairan si
Naadan si
Kis gallon meri jaan
Pareshan si?

Tenu hasde vekh ke
Baar baar
Tenu puchi na main kadey tere
Dil di saar

Tera intezar, 
Meri samjho baar 
Kidda katey ne tu din metho 
Haar haar?

C 2

Haan
Jo pyaar si tera
Thoda vi samajh na paya 
Main jhalla jhalla 

Haan
Eh dil pachtave 
Tere bin hun reh na pave 
Eh kalla kalla

A 3

Hun kyun 
Afsos hoya?
Hun ki fayeda?
Milna ni
Je chahaan chahaan

Main hun
Ghadiya de hath te
Kivein modha 
Rukh samay da 
Te rahaan rahaan?

Te rahaan rahaan
Te rahaan rahaan

Meaning of Saraswati Mantra:
Line-1: I salute Mother Saraswati who is so pure and white like that of jasmine, moon and a garland of pearls; she is the one who is adorned with sparkling white garments.
Line-2: whose hands are adorned with the Veena and boon giving staff; who is seated on a pure white lotus
Line-3: Who is always worshipped by Brahma (the creator), Achyuta (Vishnu or the protector), Shankara (Shiva or the destroyer) and all the devas (gods)
Line-4: Oh Mother Saraswati, the divine one, protect me and dispel all my ignorance

Benefit :
Regular chanting of Saraswati Mantra can clarify thoughts, improve will power and the power of self-determination, vairagya or sense of detachment. The mantra can dispel ignorance and help in the quick mastering of all that is learnt. It can install the true purpose of life in the minds of the chanters and conform them firmly in their pursuit of spiritual advancement.

Meaning of Saraswati Mantra:
Line-1: I salute Mother Saraswati who is so pure and white like that of jasmine, moon and a garland of pearls; she is the one who is adorned with sparkling white garments.
Line-2: whose hands are adorned with the Veena and boon giving staff; who is seated on a pure white lotus
Line-3: Who is always worshipped by Brahma (the creator), Achyuta (Vishnu or the protector), Shankara (Shiva or the destroyer) and all the devas (gods)
Line-4: Oh Mother Saraswati, the divine one, protect me and dispel all my ignorance

Benefit :
Regular chanting of Saraswati Mantra can clarify thoughts, improve will power and the power of self-determination, vairagya or sense of detachment. The mantra can dispel ignorance and help in the quick mastering of all that is learnt. It can install the true purpose of life in the minds of the chanters and conform them firmly in their pursuit of spiritual advancement.

About The Show:
----------------------------
Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah is a comedy show inspired by the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chashmah' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This show revolves around the Gada Family which consists of uneducated businessmen Jethalal Champaklal Gada, Jethalal‚Äôs Wife Daya & their naughty Son Tipendra Gada living in Gokuldham Co-operative Society' and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. In case of a problem and emergency, Jethalal Gada often rushes to Taarak Mehta to seek his help and guidance as he finds a philosopher in him. The housing society residents help each other find solutions when facing common, real-life challenges and getting involved in sticky situations.

snippet.title: Pre-booked Breakfast On Air India Express!! ‚úàÔ∏èüçΩÔ∏è
snippet.description:
Pre-booked a ‚Çπ650 breakfast on my Air India Express flight from Bengaluru to Delhi‚Äîwas it worth it? First, a little heartbreak‚Äîwhere‚Äôs the iconic artificial waterfall at T2? Anyway, after boarding the new Boeing 737, I found myself in a middle seat with no window (tough life). Took off with a limited outside view and soon, food arrived! T

he masala tea? Too watered down. The cheese omelette? A bit eggy at first but got better. The hara bhara kebab? Surprisingly soft and moist. The baked beans? Classic, soft, and mushy. 

But the real winner? The banana chocolate cake‚Äîdense, balanced, and a big thumbs up! Wrapped it all up with some water before dozing off, only to wake up to great weather in Delhi. Another flight, another meal reviewed‚Äîsubscribe for more food and travel adventures!
